# Target Metadata Automation (The Wow Factor)

To deliver a premium, automated UX, we will upgrade the Settings dashboard so that whenever you paste a target URL (whether it’s an exact site, a creator profile, or a community link), the system automatically reaches out to the web, grabs the site's logo or profile picture, and saves it into the configuration.

This means your table rows will transform from plain text into beautiful, recognizable lists with high-res avatars and icons, proving to the user immediately that the system has successfully "locked onto" the target.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Please review the approach for metadata fetching. Basic fetch requests might be blocked by heavy WAFs (like Cloudflare) on certain sites. Since we already have the Playwright stealth engine installed, I can either use standard lightweight `fetch` + `cheerio` for instant speed, or we can use Playwright for extreme reliability but slower resolution. I propose a **hybrid approach**: lightweight `fetch` first, falling back to basic favicon resolution, prioritizing speed for the UX. 

## Proposed Changes

---

### Phase 9: Metadata Extraction Engine

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/metadata/route.ts`
- A dedicated server-rendered endpoint that takes any `url` via a POST request.
- It will execute a quick `fetch` request, parse the HTML utilizing a lightweight HTML parser (like `cheerio`), and extract the `<meta property="og:image">` or `<link rel="icon">`.
- It returns this image URL back to the frontend.

#### [MODIFY] `src/config/targetList.json` Schema
- Expand the definitions for `exactSites` (which we will now fully expose), `communities`, and `creators` to include an `imageUrl?: string` token.

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/settings/page.tsx`
- **Expose Exact Sites**: Add a brand new interactive card specifically for pacing raw URLs ("Exact Sites").
- **Live Preview UI**: As you type a URL, the "Add Target" button logic will trigger the metadata endpoint. A loading spinner will appear, and upon success, it saves the target along with the resolved logo.
- **Enhanced Tables**: Upgrade the Shadcn `<TableRow>` mappings. We will use the native Tailwind `<Avatar>` concept (circular image wrappers) to render the fetched logos dynamically next to the target name.

